#Normality:
shapiro.test(nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "WT"])
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "WT"]
## W = 0.55498, p-value < 2.2e-16
shapiro.test(nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "MUT"])
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "MUT"]
## W = 0.70945, p-value = 0.0001482
#Mann-Whitney:
wilcox.test(x=nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "MUT"], 
                  y=nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "WT"],
                  alternative = "two.sided", 
                  paired = FALSE, 
                  conf.int = 0.95)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "MUT"] and nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "WT"]
## W = 3800.5, p-value = 0.8964
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.005333172  0.006924503
## sample estimates:
## difference in location 
##             1.7447e-05

##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "WT"]
## W = 0.2047, p-value < 2.2e-16
shapiro.test(nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "MUT"])
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "MUT"]
## W = 0.62978, p-value = 0.001241
#Mann-Whitney:
wilcox.test(x=nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "MUT"], 
                  y=nras$PSI[nras$GROUP== "WT"],
                  alternative = "two.sided", 
                  paired = FALSE, 
                  conf.int = 0.95)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "MUT"] and nras$PSI[nras$GROUP == "WT"]

## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
